Package uk.ac.ljmu.fet.cs.csw.CompetitiveMinesweeper.competition

Class TeamCompetition

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ljmu.fet.cs.csw.CompetitiveMinesweeper.competition.TeamCompetition
  • public class TeamCompetition
extends Object
    This class allows to organise a competition between various game solvers where each solver plays a set of games with everyone else in the same group. After all sets are played one can collect the results from the class in a ranked order.
    Typical calling order:
    1. constructor
    2. addToCompetitors(Class) several times (at least 3x)
    3. arrangeSets() to randomly generate the sets to be played against other competitors
    4. runSets() to run the actual competition between all participants according to the previous arrangements
    5. getRankedList() to figure out the ranking of the competition
    Author:
    "Gabor Kecskemeti, Department of Computer Science, Liverpool John Moores University, (c) 2019"
